==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Tonality
<hw>To*nal"i*ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>tonalit⟦eacute⟧</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Mus.)</fld> <def>The principle
of key in music; the character which a composition has by virtue of the
key in which it is written, or through the family relationship of all
its tones and chords to the keynote, or tonic, of the whole.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The predominance of the tonic as the link which connects all the
tones of a piece, we may, with F⟦eacute⟧tis, term the principle of
<qex>tonality</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Helmholtz.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>To-name</ent>⟦br⟧
